cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is about a new optimization method for deep learning, specifically for adaptive moment estimation methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of AdamT with state-of-the-art models on several classical real-world datasets, indicating that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the method on large-scale sparse datasets, which suggests it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents a new framework for adapting Adam-type methods, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
